format: A data frame with 606 observations on the following 9 variables.
description:
Description
Liver related laboratory data from a randomized, blind, parallel group
clinical trial with 4 doses of a drug.
title: Liver related laboratory data
reference:
Dose A is the lowest dose, dose, B the next, C the next, and D the highest
dose. The baseline values were taken prior to any treatment being received,
and the clinical trial had a single post-baseline visit.

parameters.AST.B: Aspartate aminotransferase at baseline. A numeric vector.
parameters.AST.M: Aspartate aminotransferase after treatment. A numeric vector.
parameters.dose: The treatment group (i.e. dose group). A factor with levels A B C D
parameters.TBL.M: Total bilirubin after treatment. A numeric vector.
parameters.ALP.M: Alkaline phosphatase after treatment. A numeric vector.
parameters.TBL.B: Total bilirubin at baseline. A numeric vector.
parameters.ALP.B: Alkaline phosphatase at baseline. A numeric vector.
parameters.ALT.B: Alanine aminotransferase at baseline. A numeric vector.
parameters.ALT.M: Alanine aminotransferase after treatment. A numeric vector.
